Inspired by http://weirdorconfusing.com/, the best website ever. I've laughed WAYYY too much on it.

One user makes up a product. It can be functional or funny. The next user rates the product, out of 5 stars, and writes a short review for it.

Here we go!

"Musk", the Elon Musk brand perfume/cologne/pheromone/whatever. Smells like stress sweat, rocket fuel, and burnt batteries. 20ml for $79.99

I-tag life, $399.99 . Just for extroverts

I-tag lexas, $1299.99. The phone has a built in hover feature, it follows you even when you set it in a table. To the shower, into bed, skinny dipping in the pond behind your house.

I-tag cheater, $699.99. Same as extrovert but replaces all images of love-interests with wife or girl friend

I-tag spy, $1999.99. You take a picture of the phone you want to spy on, the spy phone arrives and it switches itself with the phone downloading all the info, it then records everything the person does, sees, and sends back the information sorted to the account of the purchaser. Has a built in attorney application. 

I-tag cheater deluxe, $9999.99, as with base model but is immune to I-spy.
